364 U.S. 300

81 S.Ct. 268

5 L.Ed.2d 90

STANDARD DREDGING CORPORATION, appellant,
v.
ALABAMA.

No. 332.

Supreme Court of the United States

October 24, 1960

Eberhard P. Deutsch, Rene H. Himel, Jr., and Malcolm W. Monroe, for appellant.

MacDonald Gallion, Atty. Gen. of Alabama, Guy Sparks, Special Asst. Atty. Gen., and William H. Burton, Asst. Atty. Gen., for appellee.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.
